<DOC><DOCNO> AP890120-0107 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-20-89 1322EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Rebels     01-20 0107</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Zimbabwe-Rebels,0110</SECOND><HEAD>Border Raid Kills 7, Including Children</HEAD><DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mozambican rebels making a border raidshot and killed seven people _ five of them children _ who werefleeing into the bush, police said.   The rebels attacked Mbadza village in the northeast, about sixmiles from the border with neighboring Mozambique, on Tuesday, apolice spokesman said.   The children ranged in age from 5 to 13, said the spokesman, whospoke on condition of anonymity.   Right-wing Mozambican rebels who are fighting the Mozambicangovernment frequently cross into Zimbabwe to steal food andsupplies. Scores of Zimbabwean civilians have been killed in suchraids.</TEXT></DOC>